track_notes: This is the most popular tourist route from Keswick Town Centre to the summit. Limited free parking is available at NY 281253. You have more chance of a space very early or later in the day.
track_title: Skiddaw from Keswick Town Centre One Way

track_notes:
A full day round of 12.5m (20.1km) with 4500ft (1370m) ascent. 
Roadside parking in Applethwaite NY 260258. Climb to Dodd - Carlside - detour to Ullock Pike and return Carlside - SKIDDAW - Skiddaw Little Man - Lonscale Fell - Latrigg.
track_title: Skiddaw Round with another seven Wainwrights

track_notes: This route is from Threlkeld. I caught the bus from Keswick to Threlkeld and finished the walk at a cottage I rented near Crosthwaite roundabout - so this track stops short of Keswick Twon Centre. The route up Halls Fell ridge is a classic on the right day. If I were doing this linear route again again I would try cutting across the northern flank of Blease Fell south of Roughten Gill rather than going down to Blencathra centre. The climb up to Lonscale Fell (Wainwright) was steep but doable. Before reaching Skiddaw its mate Little Man (Wainwright) is visited. After LD-004 the slate path down to Carlside (Wainwright) is traversed.

This is an easy to follow route and is less frequented than the southern routes. 

There is parking for about 5 cars at the start.

The first section is to follow the Cumbrian Way to the top of the Whitewater Dash waterfall. Then follow the fence to near the summit. The last section to the summit is a simple path. 

It took me 1h45m to get up with kit for the 23cm UKAC.
track_title: A track to G/LD-004 Skiddaw from the north
